caption: I ordered pho noodle soup and I desperately wished it was good because I moved to fidi recently and there aren’t other pho options nearby... The noodles and beef balls were okay, but soup tasted like lightly salted water... tastes nothing like chinatown pho spots. Maybe their sandwiches are great but the soup is really subpar.  My mistake. Fish balls* not beef
Great service, great food and the guy in charge was really kind and friendly. Definitely a place to visit here in NY

Walked in here on a whim. Had the reccomended beef Pho (First time having Pho) and it quite possibly is one of the best things i've ever had in my life. The broth is buttery with lime, the meat is perfect, noodles are excellent and the sauce is just sweet enough. Perfection. Really glad to see they've surived COVID and are still cooking the best Pho in town! If you're looking for your new favorite addiction/hole in the wall place... this is it!
Great place to eat and great customer service. The staff members are super nice and friendly.
Really nice portions

A bit of a hole in the wall of a Vietnamese place, but that's what makes it a bit of a hidden gem. I got the beef pho with spicy broth and it was definitely delicious, and perhaps more importantly you get a ton of food for the price you pay (which is good because it's a little above average on the price scale at ~$14 a bowl). The one thing to note, if you don't order online ahead of time, they only take cash, but ordering online you can still use card. Wait isn't too long for any order, but it will definitely still be a little slower than your typical take out depending on what you get. I can't wait to try out more of the options they have, as everything looks and smells delicious when you walk in there.
vietnamese food... so delicious. I really loved this place. Atmosphere is like a restaurant in Fort Worth I loved.

The food is really good here, I had a half pho bowl, half sandwich special and it was really filling, even for around 16.00 after tax. If you're looking for vegan options, the tofu bowl and avocado and mushroom sandwich are 10/10

I've lived a block away for almost four years but for some reason never stopped in. Wish I had because I've been missing out on four years worth of their Classic Banh Mi. One if the best sandwiches I've had.
Good lunch pho special with Bahn mi

Do yourself a favor and get the classic banh mi with pate added. It’s one of the best I’ve had—and trust me, I’ve had a lot from all over the US and Vietnam. If you order from their site online, you can get 10% off your order.

Small place but was able to get a spot during lunch rush. Wait not too bad. Pho was decent (above average by NYC standards) but chicken was grilled and on the side which was a first for me. Overall, not bad. Will return.

My go-to pho place.  Cash only.  I know you probably think of classic beef pho when you think about pho, but try with steamed vegetables (still with the regular broth).  Loaded with broc, carrots and cabbage,  it makes for a very satisfying meal,  particularly on a cruddy rainy day.
The Pho is awesome. I always have it when I am sick.  But today I had to go get cash to order.
Very good vietnamese fast food. They pack it well for take out. Only cash accepted, but cards can be used on line.
So good

IF you're claustrophobic and don't like sitting elbow to elbow and having people standing directly behind you as you eat, this is not the place for you.  IF you refuse to carry and pay via cash, this is not the place for you.  IF you care about the décor and cleanliness of a restaurant, this place is not for you.  EEEF you like person take daa ordah speak no English and want make change to classic deesh, this no the place fo you.  IF you don't like rare beef (we're not living in the 19th century, people), this place is not for you.  IF you don't give two sheets to the wind about any of that and enjoy a clean, consistent, flavorful, delicious, authentic bowl of Pho THIS IS YOUR SPOT.

Good food at a decent price. I agree with other reviews here that say it can be hit or miss at times, but mostly it satisfies. I liked going for a quick meal on my lunch breaks at work, but they’ve recently switched to cash only. I don’t ever carry cash,  so I doubt I’ll return.

When someone coined the term “hole in the wall” they were thinking of Vietspot FiDi. I say this in the nicest way since some of the best food I have eaten and some of my favorite places fall into this category. No frills, no muss. It’s all about the food. And they usually are cash only, like Vietspot. That being said, it’s not the cheapest as far as lunch goes. $14 and change for a Pho bowl with grilled pork chops. Of course, with all the fixins - jalapeños, lime, sprouts, sauces. I got it with ramen and I’m pretty the noodles are from those ramen packets you used to eat in college. Love it. The portions are LARGE and did I say how great the food is? Talk about feel good eats. This stuff will put you on a good food high, again in a good way. Ingredients are simple and fresh. Make sure you also get an iced Vietnamese coffee. It’s an extra $5 but well worth it.
Grilled pork pho is great, much better than the beef pho! Cash only place.
Vietspot is a great spot to grab some delicious pho for lunch! Only reason it isn't a full 5 stars is because I've had a few inconsistent experiences but it's still great nonetheless.
delicious food but the chicken is too salty.
Love the pork chop bowl and brisket pho.
Banh mi here is great :D
Love their chicken pho. Order online for quick service
Very filling, great ingredients
Not the most authentic, pork chop often made up of a lot of bone but otherwise a great spot for lunch in fidi

A gem hidden in the financial district! If you’re a noodle soup lover....better yet a pho lover and you need some pho....Vietspot does not disappoint! The flavor of the broth is what you would expect. It’s clean, light, and savory. I love beef pho but they have other protein options.  They also have Banh Mi (Vietnamese sandwiches) which are also delicious.

The food has always been fantastic. I've been a few times and was never disappointed. It's definitely a popular spot, so do expect a wait during the lunch rush. However, you can pre-order online and skip the line almost entirely.
One of the best pho in Fidi!! Especially the raw beef. But they don’t take cards anymore.
Great food, friendly staff and it’s cheap. Can’t get enough!!!
Best pho around in my opinion. And the portions are big!!

Great vietnamese coffee and thai iced tea. I will swing by in the afternoons just for the beverage.  The food is out of this world too. I have never had porkchops as good as the ones they do here. The summer rolls are great too. Highly recommend getting here early for lunch to skip the lines.

The best in the neighborhood! Been working in this part of town on and off for almost 10 years and this hidden gem on a side street is worth a stop for lunch. MUST do it! Order to go because there isn't a lot of space to stay.
This place serves the best Pho in NYC. I always go for the pork chops pho, it's very flavorful!!!

I stumbled upon this place during my lunch break. I checked their menu and I decided to give it a try. As soon as I got my order, I was very happy with the portion. I thought it would be smaller for the price I paid since it’s Manhattan. I would definitely come back here and try their other menu items.

(Translated by Google) Very delicious Vietnamese style Pho, the full price is reasonable, the CP value is very high ~ people with small food can eat one person, add a spring roll Summer roll. The store is small, but the service is very warm! There are a few guests at noon during the week and it is recommended to avoid the meal. After riding the bicycle, I will come to a bowl of Vietnamese jelly, which is great! I have already visited the second time and I look forward to eating again!  (Original) 非常美味的越式河粉Pho，份量十足價錢合理CP值很高～食量小的人可以兩個人吃一份，再加點一份春捲Summer roll。店面比較小，但服務非常熱情！週間中午客人稍多，建議避過餐期來。騎完腳踏車馬上來一碗越式涼粉，非常棒！目前已經二訪，期待再一次去吃！
Hit or miss. Depending on the day you go there

Place has some seating, tight space though. Food is good and a regular price for a decent bowl of pho on a chilly day. It is cash only unless you order online ahead of time. Lime water is available for free which is nice.
Had the chicken pho, couldn't jew any meet and the beef broth was a cartoon chicken soup!
Great food.
Best phở at NY
Good place and the food,  really really... good
The onwer/ manager supper friendly! Pho here is decent as well! Worth to try again when i’m back to NY 😊

Below average. Super small place with limited seating. It seems that most people get to-go food. High prices: $14 for a bowl of pho. Serving size was decently large but taste was average. Pork was quite raw, but cooked more when I let it bathe in the soup for a while. Broth was quite bland, however. Very little richness and tasted almost like water. They gave me a metal spoon instead of a porcelain for soup, which I found odd. Service was decent, but didn’t make up for the other lacking qualities. They ran out of banh mi at 7 pm on a Tuesday. And water was self-serve and also almost empty. Pho choices weren’t that many, and didn’t have Bun Bo Hue. Wouldn’t recommend overall.  Edit: Sorry, the beef was super raw, not the pork.

This is on the FiDi location. I was looking forward to trying this spot as I was craving some crunchy spring rolls. Here is the pic of the air fried spring rolls they advertise vs what I got. This doesn't even taste like anything. Looks like they were frozen together in the freezer and separated while cooking, if it even cooked fully through. Also note, I JUST got them from the restaurant, so no they weren't sitting out long.

A tiny restaurant with max 10 places to sit but with a very decent pho. It’s a massive serving and the broth is delicious though I find it a bit pricey. Payed $14,50. Would still definitively recommend this place!
Sandwhich and spring rolls were pretty good. Broth in the Pho was very bland.
Good service, and the food was very decent too. Let me tell you: if you're in Fidi and are craving for Viet food, Vietspot is the place to go.
Great spot for lunch/dinner to grab a tasty bowl of pho
Very small space so you will probably not have room to sit. The Pho is good, not great. The Bahn Mi is incredible. Great meat and a crispy loaf.  So glad this place is in the neighborhood.
The best FIDI place have Pho and Thai ice tea!
I love their chicken meatball banh mi and Vietnamese iced coffee so much I've never tried anything else! Super busy at lunch.
One of my favorite lunch spots — the tofu pho is excellent. The seating inside is limited, but clears up pretty fast. No frills, quick and delicious.

Great portion size for $14. I got the beef pho towards the end of the night but my soup was strangely bland and it was unexpected cause everyone else seemed to have a great experience. Maybe it was an off day
Uncommon to see Vietnamese food in Fidi, but enough choices and interior space to recommend.  Also coupons on emailed receipts are a delightful treat.
Recommend beat pho and pork chop bowl! All sauces are good to add.
Amazing Bánh mì. Love visiting here whenever Im in a tasty pork mood.
Awesome food and great service with a smile :)

I didnt like the food. The meat was hot but the noodles were cold, the soda was warm. everything was covered in bits of parsley, everything tasted like parsley. The Noodle bowl wasnt served in broth, they put some kind of oil on the side but it just smelled like white wine vinegar. The price for a bowl is $11 according to the menu they have posted, but with my order and a can of soda it came to $14.75, and i was unsatisfied.
Bahn mi was deliciously fresh, warm and toasty and pho was flavorful. Good vibe and quick service!
Food was alright but very convenient! Will come back.
Thus far, best bah-mi I've had in the city. The mushroom avocado bah-mi was delicious and a great complement to the beef shank Phõ!
As Vietnamese, I give this place 6 stars. Good vibe, staff are all super friendly. A bowl of pho will bright your day no matter how tired you are!

The food is strangely bland now, I don't know whether people eat their food on days that it is better or they generally don't know what real Vietnamese food is. This is a true rip off to what the place looks like and how the management of this place is. Too disappointed.
Excellent pho and bahn mi
Good food, the owner is super nice and friendly... for sure I will come back when I am in town next time

Best Vietnamese restaurant in town. I'm from LA, California so I'm very picky with Vietnamese food but this place is awesome. Very high quality food for a very penny price in the center of the city. I got a bowl for take a way for lunch. There is "protein" dish here which means you can order the meat only. For those who is working out like me it's great. I can just order some grill chicken with steam vegi. The sauce is extremely delicious. You should try "banh mi" too. I can eat here couple times a week.
I like the sandwich here a lot since it's warm toasted but doesn't hurt my gum, I tried a few other Vietnamese places, the banh mi crust is too hard it hurts my mouth.
My company moved down to this area so I have been discovering new food for lunch. Lucky to find out this place has one of the best grilled chicken pho I ever tasted!

If I could give this place six stars I would. We found it by chance less than a block away from our hotel and I'm going to have to force myself to give other places a chance. The food here is amazing, the portions are huge, and the prices are fantastic. I seriously think this is a must try. There is some against the wall hightop seating but it it's a pretty small space. The chicken meatball pho and earl gray milk tea is really fantastic.
The broth in the pho is amongst the best I've tasted. This hole in the wall definitely delivered beyond all my expectations.

Pho is good, broth always tasty, the most thing I love about this place is they are real Vietnamese people speaking Vietnamese to each other, also they put the culantro and thai basil and lost of scallions in the pho just like in Vietnam... I went there and found out that nobody there ever put the cilantro in the pho? what the pho?

Very good banh mi! This is place is fairly small but clean and great for takeout. It is right next to the WTC, fairly convenient spot.  I got the grilled pork banh mi and it was very tasty. The pork was freshly grilled and well seasoned, slightly sweet. There were a few fatty bits which I didn't love but your taste may vary so I'm not taking points off for that. The veggies were good and it was fairly mild for "spicy" (although you can get non-spicy).  Prices are a little bit on the high side for Vietnamese food but appropriate for the area, you won't really find anything cheaper here. Recommended!
I just order on their website and pick up for 10% off, also I don't have to wait in line!

I tend to get banh mi here earlier than noon. Sometimes I take out a bowl of jasmine rice with tofu and veggies after work. I love their tofu! Shrimp is also fresh and buttery. Wish they can give me steamed veggies for free but it's $2.5 extra. :-/
Great pho. Hard to find but worth the search. Attentive service. 🌠🌠🌠🌠🌠
Always delicious here. Great and fast service. Reasonable prices.

I got the traditional Bánh Mì, spicy, on whole wheat (making it less traditional, I know 😆). It was flavorful and we'll balanced! The bread was perfect -- crispy crust, soft inside. I would come back!  I later got the grilled chicken on Vietnamese salad. I gotta say that I was not a fan of the chicken....
Ok food. mmm.... good.

Since I am a visitor to NYC, I thought I would give it a try as it was snowing. Very Poor Service I had ever experienced in a long time or should I say "No Service". It is a fast food "Self-Service" restaurant. After I seated myself, I went to the counter to order since I did not see anyone attending. I was asked to pay first when ordering and when I inserted my credit card, the options for tips were 15%, 20% or others. As I had to serve myself including pouring the water, I paid a $2 tip. When my number was called, I picked up the order myself. The food was just average as I had tried better Pho at some places including my recent visit to Las Vegas. I would not have written this review if it ended just like that. What prompted me to write was that when I was preparing to leave with my son, the girl at the counter said "Can you help me bring the tray and bowl?" I took my tray and bowl to her anyway; good thing she did not ask me to clean up the table because I would definitely have asked  "why do you set up your machine for a 15% or 20% and have a tip bowl at the counter if you don't provide any service at all? Give me my tip back!" If you behave like a fast food restaurant like Burger King, do NOT ask customers nor expect any tip then!
Great pho. They always forget half my order
Best banh mi sandwiches in a tiny spot that's easy to miss
Good pho, tight space, fast service and good prices

I don’t get that here’s been highly rated. We ordered pork-chop sandwich but it was nearly stone. Moreover, the service was just horrible. They didn’t greet us at the first time. The communication was so poor as well. It seemed that they don’t understand their job. We felt very unpleasant.
This place was very authentic

Pho was ok. Ordered a combo with pho and summer rolls and they were left out of my order. Tried to call multiple times and no one picked up and the voicemail is full.  I was contacted by the owner and fully refunded for my meal. I am anxious to try it again I have adjusted my Review and will revisit after going to the restaurant again

Single worst meal I’ve had in 6 years in New York. Banh mi smelled like actual balls and the steamed veggies were only salvageable because they were flavorless and I could put hoisin on it. Go anywhere else

Generous portion size compared to what’s pictured on the website (for a pork chop rice). Tastes good, might have gotten cold from my walk back to the office. I ordered online and it was ready when I got there.
Just get a cup of noodle at a grocery store

So far, I've been to the Church Street location twice. They serve up an excellent pho. The spicy beef broth is terrific -- flavorful, tangy, and piping hot -- and the accompanying ingredients are fresh and tastey. On my first visit during their opening week, the bahn mi was good, though they could have been more generous with the pork portioning -- a minor detail. Regardless, this is a welcome fast casual option for the neighborhood with authentic flavors and friendly service. I strongly recommend it if you want Vietnamese on the go.
It wasn’t the greatest pho I’ve ever tasted but it kept me warm. I wouldn’t recommend this place for authentic pho.
Food is good, but very small and always pack
Very crowded during the lunch rush. Food is ok, nothing to write home about.

“Our food is not prepared by order. We do this in the fastest way. OK?” What they told me after I waited for more than 15 minutes and see people came much later and get my food before me. It seems “Fastest” is for ALL customers not for me. Vietspot did get 4+ rate here for ALL. Sorry for me it’s only 1 star. Terrible service!
Good is gross. Not even fresh. The soup came like warm so the noodles were still hard. How are your air fried spring rolls so greasy? This place is disgusting.
Excellent bahn mi and Vietnamese coffee

(Translated by Google) If you want cheap eat and Vietnamese experience. Order beef pho and typical sandwich  (Original) Si quieres comer barato y experiencia vietnamita. Pide pho de ternera y sándwich típico
Best shrimp Pho i have ever ate.
Very good Bonmi but was out of a number of dishes like chx meatballs.
Beat Pho I've ever had. Delicious.
It's a hole in the wall, packed during lunch, and exactly what I want.
Nothing special- the website makes it look super fancy but ultimately was just basic Vietnamese takeout. The Thai iced tea was good but the Vermicelli bowl was overpriced for what it was.
(Translated by Google) Great train mi  (Original) Great bahn mi
Good pho and w Quick service
Best pork chop rice bowl ever
Overpriced and crowded. Plus there is bones in their chicken pho

No frills, quicker than going to Chinatown, but for $10.50 for a bowl of beef pho, I'd expect better broth. I've been going here for a while and feel the broth lately has only a black pepper taste. Not much flavor,  one dimensional, and only better after adding lime and hoisin. If you're in FiDi and need a quick pho, I'd suggest the Bahn Mi Cart or even OBAO, but if you can't make it down towards Water St, Vietspot may satisfied the pho craving.
Excellent service, kind staff, happy to serve you. Delicious pho.
So delicious Vietnamese beef pho !
A great spot for lunch or after. Delicious food accompanied by great service.

Very crowded at lunch? But service was fast and we even got a seat.  Not many choices for Vietnamese in this area - so it was the only choice.  It was good - not great.  I live near many Vietnamese restaurants - so I've had great.  We got the pho and bun (vermicelli noodles). I've also had the pho on one other occasion.  I would eat there again if I'm craving Vietnamese.

How anyone can actually like this place is beyond me.... Completely flavorless broth (more like water), sub-par ingredients,  nasty summer rolls. And the pho gave me stomach issues immediately after consumption. Tried it once,  never again.
Nice food and the price is good

Amazing place to grab a quick bite. Delicious food with friendly staff.  Small and cozy with extraordinary food. Order to pick up or come in and sit down.  I love this place and hope anyone who likes authentic Vietnamese food try this diamond in the rough. Do not judge the small location bur instead just enjoy the food.
Good for lunch and the space is narrow
Food is okay. But the soap is a little bit plain..
Solid pho downtown
Had beef pho. The broth was very very bland and the beef was very tough
I come here all the time in the winter for the great chicken pho and summer rolls. The service is awesome and the food is prepared quickly!
the best pho place in fidi, good bahnmi too
Good Vietnamese food. A regular lunch spot. Very small area so don't plan to stay too long. A few seats though do exist. Recommend the Vietnamese sandwich. Very pleasant service.

(Translated by Google) Small place but you can hopefully find a space to eat right there. But the food they prepare is very good, the Pho and the traditional sandwich they serve are very good. If you are not very hungry, the combo can be the best offer. Good food and not so expensive.  (Original) Lugar pequeño pero puedes encontrar con suerte un espacio para comer ahí mismo. Pero la comida que preparan es muy buena, el Pho y el sandwich tradicional que sirven son muy buenos. Si no tienes mucha hambre, los combo pueden ser la mejor oferta. Comida buena y no tan caro.

I went in, ordered a pho with mushrooms to go, waited 5 minutes and went out. I paid $11 (tax included). Bring cash because credit card minimum is $15!! The pho was good! If you decide to stay there’s high chairs to enjoy you food!
Excellent banh mis and pho. Very fast and effective service. The place is comfortable enough to eat in.

Unfortunately,  this place does NOT hit the ( viet) spot.  The Pho ($10 a bowl )lacks everything that makes it ... Pho. Luke war broth is bland, the noodles are rubbery and so is the chicken. They try, but   The cashier is nice and service is pleasant, the portion is  decent,  but they have to step it up learn how to properly prepare pho.   Don't  recommend this place at all.  Save your money.
Grill chicken pho is the best!!
Very fresh and tasty... excellent service! Highly recommended.
Quick and tasty pho and banh mi. Stools and counters are available for dining-in. No tables for larger parties
Loved their vegetarian Banh mi sandwich. Very small place, line goes out of the store during lunch hours.
Authentic  vietnamese cuisine with excellent traditional phõ. Unexpected in wall street!

I was pleasantly surprised with this place. The banh mi was quite good - the bread is excellent - crispy but easy to bite and doesn't poke your gums. And the filling is good as well, tasty pork, veggies and sauce. It is a bit pricey though and you don't get a lot of food, but if you're not terribly hungry it's a good option.
Great pho. Very delicious food for adorable price. Minimum $15 credit card charge. Not much room to sit and eat but a clean restaurant and great food and service
Great banh mi sandwich, very filling for the price. Not an ideal place to sit for a meal, definitely more of a takeout place.
This place has great Pho and amazing Banh Mi 😘
Solid sandwiches and pho, it's not great but it's definitely good.
I ate here so many times, delicious food and great services. Strongly recommend.

I think the sandwiches are probably the go to for this place as I've had them a few times and have not been disappointed.  Today, I had some time and ate in and had the grilled chicken pho and I guess it was chicken stock.  I'm used to having beef stock so expect it to be more flavorful, so that could have been it.  Most Vietnamese places I go to have the grilled chicken or pork whole, but they cut it into strips for you here for convenience that is definitely a plus IMO.  Will try the beef pho the next time I'm in this area on a weekday, but for now recommend the sandwiches over the pho.  The pho came with the usual accoutrements,  basil, bean sprouts, lime.
Enjoyed the grilled chicken pho; small place and gets crowded around lunchtime.

I work nearby here and this is one of my FAVE lunch spots. I have only ever gotten the tofu pho because it is soooooo good I've never wanted to try anything else. It's also super filling which is awesome cause I usually feel hungry after soups. The tofu is a great texture - not soft and slimey, but has a more natural texture, and has an amazing glaze on it. I usually get this and a thai iced tea and it's truly amazing.
Nice lil place with good food
Great Pho. Quick service
The best food downtown!!!!

The first time I had Pho was in South Africa and this Pho is my favorite of all that I have tried. The Pork Chop Pho is my favorite with the 2nd being Chicken. May theyou flourish and have more locations!

I have been a loyal raw beef Pho fan, until the day I tried pork chop Pho. Vietspot serves delicious food in general, haven't found another Vietnamese place near by can compete with the price and food quality.
This place has had a bunch of names, but has consistently served up the same amazing chicken sandwich. Great lunch spot.
The tofu pho is amazing. Some of the best tofu I've ever had, hands down.
Great food, fast service, reasonable price
I like this place so much because there are good sandwiches and noodles!
Simple and satisfying!
